<h2> Welcome to my Portfolio! </h2>
<h3>Who am I?</h3>
<p>My name is Ekim Tektas, and I am currently working towards getting my second Master's in English Literature. I am currently an English teacher at a high school in Fairfax County Public Schools. This year I worked with freshmen (Class of 2029) and sophomores (Class of 2028). It was a pleasure working with them this since I was able to see them grow as individuals! </p>
<p>As an educator, at the beginning of the year, we are tasked with creating a goal we would like students to achieve prior to the end of the year. My goal was for students to improve on their written communication since there is a current stagnation for students to write because of consistent use of spellcheck and not having the stamina for it.</p>
<p> When I am not a teacher or a student at George Mason University; I am having fun! Some of the things that I like doing are:</p>
<ul>
<li>Playing Pokémon Games (and collecting cards solely for nostalgia)</li>
<li>Playing Fire Emblem on my Switch</li>
<li>Hanging out with friends</li>
<li>Annoying my pets (pet tax [insert hyperlink to pictures])</i>
<li>Creative Writing</li>
<li>Reading (my favorite genres are dystopia and fantasy)</li>
</ul>
<p>Adding onto the creative writing hobby of mine, one of my goals before I graduate (or a little after I do) is to publish my own dystopian novel.</p>
